import { Component } from '@angular/core'; import { Emitters } from '../emiters/emitters'; import { HttpClient } from '@angular/common/http'; import { Router } from '@angular/router'; @Component({ selector: 'app-profile', templateUrl: './profile.component.html', styleUrls: ['./profile.component.css'] }) export class ProfileComponent { message:any=""; id:any=""; name : any; email: any; auth=false; admin=false constructor(private http: HttpClient, private router: Router) { } ngOnInit(): void { this.http.get('http://localhost:8000/api/user', {withCredentials: true}).subscribe( (res: any) => { this.message = `Hi ${res.name}`; this.name = `${res.name}`; this.id = `${res.id}`; this.email = `${res.email}`; console.log(res) if (res.admin_access==1){ Emitters.adminEmitter.emit(true); this.message=this.message+ " You're an admin"; } Emitters.authEmitter.emit(true); } ); Emitters.authEmitter.subscribe( (data: any) => { this.auth= data; console.log("This is working1"); } ); Emitters.adminEmitter.subscribe( (data: any) => { this.admin= data; console.log("This is working2"); } ); } logout(): void { this.http.post('http://localhost:8000/api/logout', {}, {withCredentials: true}) .subscribe((succ: any) => { this.auth = false console.log(succ) this.router.navigate(['/login']) }); } goToLogin(): void { this.router.navigate(['/login']); } }
